{"title":"Ritchey Adds Integrated Stems & Headsets, Shallow Gravel Bar, New Colors, and More!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/ritchey-internal-routing-stems-corralitos-gravel-handlebar/","date":1679527278000,"content":"<p>Even the classic brands are moving forward with the most modern of trends. Ritchey has two new headsets coming that accommodate full internal routing through the upper cup, with a road stem that hides them for an even cleaner look.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s also new colors for the Ascent and Breakaway frames, a new MTB stem, and its shallowest gravel adventure bar yet.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ritchey Comp Corralitos Handlebar</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-05.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-05-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Corralitos alloy gravel adventure bike handlebar with shallow drop\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-05-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-05-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-05-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-05-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-05-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-05.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Offering the shallowest drop Ritchey has ever done, the new Corralitos is a wide alloy riser drop handlebar with tons of flare. It’s designed for any adventure; whether that’s around town or around the world, there’s a lot of space for bags and gear between the drops.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-07.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-07-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Corralitos alloy gravel adventure bike handlebar with shallow drop\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-07-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-07-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-07-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-07-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-07-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-07.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/ritchey-skyline-ergonomic-road-bike-handlebar/\">recent Skyline road bar</a>, it’s starting at the Comp level with double-butted 6061 alloy. If they prove popular, then it’ll add WCS and carbon versions later.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-06.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-06-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Corralitos alloy gravel adventure bike handlebar with shallow drop\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-06-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-06-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-06-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-06-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-06-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-corralitos-comp-shallow-gravel-handlebar-06.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Drop is just 67.5 mm, with a short 52mm reach. It has a round top to make accessory mounting easier but gets its ergonomic bend in the drops. Other measurements are:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>24º drop flare</li>\n\n\n\n<li>12º outward flare</li>\n\n\n\n<li>5º backsweep</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Widths: 46/48/50 cm (center to center)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Width at ends: 62/64/66 cm (at outside edge)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>350 g (46 cm)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Pricing and availability are TBA.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-breakaway-travel-road-bike-frame-sand-tan-blue-01.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-breakaway-travel-road-bike-frame-sand-tan-blue-01-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"New Cornflower Blue color for Ritchey Breakaway travel road bike frame\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-breakaway-travel-road-bike-frame-sand-tan-blue-01-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-breakaway-travel-road-bike-frame-sand-tan-blue-01-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-breakaway-travel-road-bike-frame-sand-tan-blue-01-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-breakaway-travel-road-bike-frame-sand-tan-blue-01-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-breakaway-travel-road-bike-frame-sand-tan-blue-01-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-breakaway-travel-road-bike-frame-sand-tan-blue-01.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Note the new sand/tan colorway for the Ascent gravel bike shown up top. That and this marine/cornflower blue with cream accents on the Breakaway travel road bike frame are new for 2023.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And yes, that <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/ritchey-ultra-mountain-bike-returns-retro-red-white-blue-team-fade-for-50th-anniversary/\">50th Anniversary Ultra</a> hardtail that just came out was the last of the limited-edition bikes celebrating Tom’s half-century milestone. Turns out supplier issues and paint lead times helped stretch that celebration beyond the actual 50th year, but who doesn’t enjoy a good, long party?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ritchey Integrated Stems &amp; Headsets</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-switch-stem-integrated-headset-01.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-switch-stem-integrated-headset-01-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"ritchey comp switch stem with integrated cable cover and stem for internal cable routing on bicycle frames\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-switch-stem-integrated-headset-01-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-switch-stem-integrated-headset-01-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-switch-stem-integrated-headset-01-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-switch-stem-integrated-headset-01-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-switch-stem-integrated-headset-01-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-switch-stem-integrated-headset-01.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Comp Switch Stem is a streamlined road stem that uses its C220 clamp (the body of the stem wraps around 220º of the bar for a more secure grip — most bars are 180º), but with a wider body for increased torsional stiffness compared to its round stems. Available in 80/90/100/110/120 mm lengths with -16º rise. Claimed weight is 180 g (100 mm).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The underside has a channel to make room for shift cables, wires, and brake hoses, which are then hidden by the upper transition spacer plate on the new Comp Logic-E Switch Headset. The nylon and glass-fiber spacers and plate conceal all of the cables and run them through the oversized 1.5″ bearing cups (fits standard tapered and 1-1/8″ steerers).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Zero Stack headset uses sealed angular cartridge bearings for smooth operation. Its weight is 54 g (upper portion only, it works with any lower bottom bracket cup).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-logic-e-universal-integrated-headset-03.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-logic-e-universal-integrated-headset-03-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Logic-E Universal Switch headset with internal routing ports\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-logic-e-universal-integrated-headset-03-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-logic-e-universal-integrated-headset-03-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-logic-e-universal-integrated-headset-03-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-logic-e-universal-integrated-headset-03-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-logic-e-universal-integrated-headset-03-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-logic-e-universal-integrated-headset-03.jpg 1800w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For mountain bikes and others without fully integrated cockpits, there’s a Comp Logic-E Universal Switch model that simply puts external ports on the upper headset spacer cover, making room to feed cables and hoses into the frame. Available in Semi-Integrated (IS) and Fully Integrated (ZS) versions, it works with any standard stem.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-trail-35-stem-01.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"296\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-trail-35-stem-01-800x296.jpg\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Trail 35 mountain bike stem with offset bar clamp to adjust height\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-trail-35-stem-01-800x296.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-trail-35-stem-01-297x110.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-trail-35-stem-01-120x44.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-trail-35-stem-01-768x284.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-trail-35-stem-01-1536x569.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/ritchey-logic-comp-trail-35-stem-01.jpg 1620w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Comp Trail 35 mountain bike stem is 3D-forged 6061 alloy, fits 35mm handlebars, and uses an offset bar clamp. It can be run with the offset up or down, letting you raise or lower your cockpit by 5 mm from the center. Available in 35/45/55/65 mm lengths, the claimed weight is 135 g (35 mm).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All products are coming this spring — we got a sneak peek at Taipei Cycle Show — so pricing and ship dates for all are TBA.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.ritcheylogic.com\" target=\"_blank\">RitcheyLogic.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/ritchey-internal-routing-stems-corralitos-gravel-handlebar/\">Ritchey Adds Integrated Stems &amp; Headsets, Shallow Gravel Bar, New Colors, and More!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d45bb3995cc4dd1f5ebe0dfceebc0b9aa6782ef1805dad5542d7959a5f33cf30","category":"Cycling"}